This script plots the following type of graphics:

Usual plot
===========
./draw -T 0 -t titulo -x rotulo_x -y rotulo_y -s file.png file1.data
file2.data file3.data ...

Errorbar
========
./draw -T 1 -t titulo -x rotulo_x -y rotulo_y -s file.png file1.data
file2.data file3.data ...

Normal with steps (for ladder graph)
====================================
./draw -T 2 -t titulo -x rotulo_x -y rotulo_y -s file.png file1.data
file2.data file3.data ...


Usual Normalized plot (in porcentage)
=====================
./draw -T 3 -t titulo -x rotulo_x -y rotulo_y -s file.png file1.data
file2.data file3.data ...

Errorbar Normalized plot (in porcentage)
=====================
./draw -T 4 -t titulo -x rotulo_x -y rotulo_y -s file.png file1.data
file2.data file3.data ...

Errorbar Embedded normalized subplot
====================================
./draw -T 5 -t titulo -x rotulo_x -y rotulo_y -s file.png file1.data
file2.data file3.data ...

Errorbar Embedded normalized subplot2
=====================================
./draw -T 6 -t titulo -x rotulo_x -y rotulo_y -s file.png file1.data
file2.data file3.data ...

where -t defines the graph title, -x the x_axis title, -y the y_axis title and
-s the filename. By default the script only shows the graphic, it doesn't save
it
